1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,770
Chapter 10 Get the Action Habit Here's something leaders in every field agree on.

2
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:14,929
There is a shortage of top-flight, expertly qualified persons to fill key positions.

3
00:00:15,199 --> 00:00:19,569
There really is, as the saying goes, plenty of room at the top.

4
00:00:19,920 --> 00:00:28,530
As one executive explained, there are many almost qualified people, but there is one success ingredient often missing,

5
00:00:28,639 --> 00:00:32,929
that is, the ability to get things done, to get results.

6
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:39,889
Every big job, whether it be operating a business, high-level selling, in science,

7
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:44,609
the military, or the government, requires a man who thinks action.

8
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:52,450
Principal executives looking for a key person demand answers to questions like, will he do the job?

9
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,370
Will he follow through?

10
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:56,370
Is he a self-starter?

11
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:59,810
Can he get results or is he just a talker?

12
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:06,130
All these questions have one aim, to find out if the fellow is a man of action.

13
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,170
Excellent ideas are not enough.

14
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:19,250
An only fair idea acted upon and developed is one hundred percent better than a terrific idea that dies because it isn't followed up.

15
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:26,850
The great self-made merchant John Wanamaker often said, Nothing comes merely by thinking about it.

16
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:28,289
Think of it.

17
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:37,569
Everything we have in this world, from satellites to skyscrapers to baby food, is just an idea acted upon.

18
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:45,890
As you study people, both the successful and the just average, you find they fall into two classes.

19
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:48,289
The successful are active.

20
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,929
We'll call them activationists.

21
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:55,970
The just average, the mediocre, the unsuccessful, are passive.

22
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:58,690
We'll call them passivationists.

23
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:04,050
We can discover a success principle by studying both groups.

24
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:06,770
Mr. Activationist is a doer.

25
00:02:06,879 --> 00:02:12,130
He takes action, gets things done, follows through on ideas and plans.

26
00:02:12,479 --> 00:02:15,490
Mr. Passivationist is a donter.

27
00:02:15,599 --> 00:02:21,010
He postpones doing things until he has proved he shouldn't or can't do them,

28
00:02:21,039 --> 00:02:22,850
or until it's too late.

29
00:02:23,679 --> 00:02:29,100
The difference between Mr. Activationist and Mr. Passivationist shows through in countless little ways.

